85-103 Johnson Street, north side, from Jay to Lawrence Streets.

July 5, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

Johnson Street, north side, from Jay to Pearl Streets, showing the rear of a row of very old frame and brick dwellings fronting on the aforementioned side of the thoroughfare. The view is southwestward from Jay Street. In the background is the Montague Court Building.

P. L. Sperr

View 2: August 23, 1939
View 3: Sept. 6, 1939

View 5: N.W. Corner Johnson St. and Fleet Place.
